<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Sikkim</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">India's Organic <em>Mountain Paradise</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Sikkim, India's organic state, is a pristine Himalayan gem representing sustainable development and environmental consciousness. Nestled between Nepal and Bhutan with Tibet to the north, Sikkim showcases breathtaking mountains, lush forests and serene monasteries. The state is India's first fully organic state, reflecting deep environmental commitment and sustainable agricultural practices. From the snow-capped Kanchenjunga peak to verdant valleys, from vibrant Gangtok capital to tranquil Kanyakumari Temple, Sikkim offers spiritual and natural experiences. Known for religious harmony where Buddhist, Hindu and Christian traditions coexist peacefully, Sikkim represents India's pluralistic values. The state's diverse communities, exquisite handicrafts, warm hospitality and unique cuisine create an authentic travel experience.</p>
</section>

<section id="weather" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lWeather">Climate &amp; Best Time</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Sikkim</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Sikkim experiences monsoon (May-September), pleasant autumn (October-November), cold winter (December-February) and mild spring (March-April). March to May and September to November offer ideal weather with clear skies, comfortable temperatures and excellent visibility for mountain views and trekking.</p>
  <div class="wgrid" id="wGrid"></div>
</section>

